meta:
  origin:
    producer: World Bank Poverty and Inequality Platform
    title: 'World Bank Poverty and Inequality Platform (PIP): Percentiles'
    description: |-
      The _Poverty and Inequality Platform: Percentiles_ database reports 100 points ranked according to the consumption or income distributions for country-year survey data available in the World Bank’s [Poverty and Inequality Platform](https://pip.worldbank.org/home) (PIP). As of March 24, 2025, a total of 2,584 country-year data points, which include 2,403 distributions based on microdata, [binned data](https://datanalytics.worldbank.org/PIP-Methodology/acquiring.html#selection), or imputed/synthetic data, and 181 based on [grouped data](https://datanalytics.worldbank.org/PIP-Methodology/acquiring.html#grouped). For the grouped data, the percentiles are derived by fitting a parametric Lorenz distribution following [Datt (1998)](https://ageconsearch.umn.edu/record/94862/). For ease of communication, all distributions are referred to as survey data henceforth, and the welfare variable is referred to as income.

      We modified the original files available in [World Bank's Databank](https://datacatalog.worldbank.org/search/dataset/0063646/_poverty_and_inequality_platform_pip_percentiles) to include distributions from regions with data available in PIP's API.
    citation_full: |-
      - World Bank (2026). Poverty and Inequality Platform: percentiles [Data set]. World Bank Group. https://pip.worldbank.org/.
      - World Bank (2026). Poverty and Inequality Platform (version 20260324_2021 and 20260324_2017) [Data set]. World Bank Group. https://pip.worldbank.org/.
    version_producer: Version 16
    url_main: https://datacatalog.worldbank.org/search/dataset/0063646/_poverty_and_inequality_platform_pip_percentiles
